# Both the BioModels SBML (full keep-set, ~270 MB) and the curated SED-ML
# protocols (~49 MB) are materialized locally and NEVER committed — they would
# bloat git history permanently. Both are re-placed byte-for-byte by
# materialize.py from local sources ($BIOMODELS_SBML_DIR / $BIOMODELS_SEDML_DIR,
# the temp-biomodels mirror, PMC12677764). Local copies in a working checkout
# are expected and correct; they just stay out of version control.
*.xml
*.sedml
